section.def:
firm (律師行) means the firm
            as from time to time constituted, whether of a sole practitioner or a partnership,
            carrying on the Practice;

first Master Policies (首份總保單) means the 2 professional indemnity insurance
            policies entered into between the Society and authorized insurers effective on 1 October
            1986;

paragraph.content:
all professional fees, remuneration, commission and charges of any kind
                    whatsoever which are rendered in connection with the indemnified’s Practice;
                    and

section.def:
principal (主管) means a
            partner or sole practitioner of a firm and shall also include any solicitor holding out
            as such a partner or sole practitioner;

Professional Indemnity Scheme (專業彌償計劃) means the professional indemnity scheme set out
            in these rules, as from time to time amended by agreement between the Society and the
            Company;

second Master Policies (第二份總保單) means the 3 professional indemnity insurance
            policies entered into between the Society and authorized insurers effective on 1 October
            1987;

subparagraph.content:
the amount of any claim paid under or in respect of a policy of
                                insurance other than the former Master Policy or the Master Policies
                                or Master Policy;

paragraph.content:
any information or other matter on the basis of which any adjustment in
                    contribution is assessed in accordance with paragraph
                    2(1)(b)(iv);

the calculation of the amount of any claim paid and claims loading under
                        paragraph 2(6) and all matters which are to be included or
                    excluded when establishing the amount of claims paid;

from the date on which the outstanding balance is due and payable or
                        from any later date as the Company may specify in the written demand;
                        and

to deposit or invest in such manner as the Company may determine all or any
                    part of the fund, including any interest, dividends, profits, gains or other
                    assets accruing to or acquired by the fund;

subparagraph.content:
the first $20,000 of any one claim where he was in Practice as a
                            sole practitioner at the date when he ceased to be a solicitor in
                            Practice in Hong Kong;

the first $10,000 of any one claim where he was in Practice as a
                            partner at the date when he ceased to be a solicitor in Practice in Hong
                            Kong;

if such former solicitor was in Practice as a sole practitioner
                            immediately before he ceased to be a solicitor in Practice in Hong Kong,
                            $550,000;

the first $30,000 of any one claim where he was in Practice as a
                            sole practitioner at the date when he ceased to be a solicitor in
                            Practice;

the first $20,000 of any one claim where he was in Practice as a
                            partner at the date when he ceased to be a solicitor in Practice in Hong
                            Kong;
